condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :4.01 (a) | Description :CEC shall perform any of its obligations under the CEC Inter-Institutional Agreement. |Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :4.01 (b) | Description :The Borrower or any other authority having jurisdiction shall take any action for themodification, dissolution or disestablishmentof the Social Cabinet. | Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :4.01 (c) | Description :The Borrower or any other authority having jurisdiction shall take any action for themodification, dissolution or disestablishmentof the SIUBEN | Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Section 1 D. | Description :The Borrower, through the Social Cabinet and its National Civil Registry, shallreview and adjust annually the costs of salaries used to produce and issue the identity docs. | Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Section II A (1) | Description :The Borrower shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepareProject Reports in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.08 of the Operational Manual. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Section II A (2) | Description :The Borrower shall carry out an in-depth review (the Mid-Term Review) jointlywith the Bank not later than two years after the effective Date or such later date as the Bank shall agree, on the progres | DueDate :03-Feb-2014

Finance Agreement :Section II B (2) | Description :Without limitation on the provisions of Part A of this Section, the Borrowershall prepare and furnish to the Bank not later than 30 days after each calendar semester, audit reports | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
